image_analysis.description: A scanned page from a document containing four photographs with corresponding captions. The top left photo shows Jeffrey Epstein with Ghislaine Maxwell. The top right photo shows Jeffrey Epstein with Adrianna Ross. The middle photo is a booking photo of Jeffrey Epstein. The bottom photo is an aerial view of a facility called The Stockade. A document identifier is present at the bottom of the page.
image_analysis.layout: The page is arranged in a four-quadrant style with images and text. An image of Epstein and Maxwell is in the upper left with a caption below it. An image of Epstein and Ross is in the upper right with a caption to its left. A booking photo of Epstein is in the middle right with a caption below it. An aerial photo of a facility is in the lower left with a caption to its right. A document number is centered at the very bottom.

text_extraction.full_text:
On the day the police investigation
began, Epstein was photographed
with Ghislaine Maxwell in New York
City at the 2005 Wall Street concert
series benefiting Wall Street Rising,
at Cipriani in New York City, March
15, 2005. (Joe Shildhorn / Patrick
McMullen)

Jeffrey Epstein, photographed
with Adrianna Ross, attend-
ing the launch of Radar
magazine held at the Hotel
QT in New York City, May
2005 (Neil Rasmus / Patrick-
McMullan.com / Sipa Press)

2008 Palm Beach County Sheriff's Office
booking photo of Jeffrey Epstein (Palm
Beach County Sheriff's Office)

The Stockade, where Epstein
served his sentence, photographed
here in 2006, was located at 673
Fairgrounds Road in West Palm
Beach, Florida. At the time, it was
used as a minimum- and medium-
security facility housing women and
juveniles, as well as male inmates
on a work-release program. (Smith
Aerial Photos)
